Michelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Jaci</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/25/03 6:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Prayers and thanks</span><hr size=1> Dear Jaci, Dan, Sam, and Heidi<br>
May the peace of Christ be with you all on your journeys.  Thank you for your generosity in sharing this stage of life so freely.  You are teaching all of us so much about the power of love over death and the power of faith over despair.  We will continue to pray.<br>
In His name,<br>
Jerilyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Bud  Barb</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/25/03 8:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Prayers &amp; Love</span><hr size=1> You are all constantly in our thoughts &amp; prayers.You are such a remarkable man Dan Jaci must be so proud of you,likewise Sam &amp; Heidi,my heart just goes out to you all.May God Bless you &amp; the whole family.Hugs all around.We love you all.Bud &amp; Barb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbudignet.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slb22000>slb22000</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF9300>(4/25/03 9:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Prayers &amp; Love</span><hr size=1> Because Jaci is music to me.  I share this song:<br>
<br>
My life flows on in endless song<br>
Above earth's lamentations<br>
I hear the real, though far off hymn<br>
That hails a new creation.  Through all the tumult and the strife<br>
I hear its music ringing,<br>
It sounds an echo in my soul.<br>
How can I keep from singing?<br>
Although the tempest loudly roars,<br>
I hear the truth it liveth,<br>
And though the darkness round me close,<br>
Songs in the night it giveth.<br>
No storm can shake my inmost calm,<br>
While to this rock I'm clinging<br>
Since love is lord of heaven and earth,<br>
How can I keep from singing?<br>
<br>
I will sing this song for my sister and for Dan and Sam and Heidi as long as I have strength.  <br>
<br>
Skies, get ready for a brilliant star, waiting to be born...<br>
<br>
Love, Susan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Charlotte</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/26/03 2:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Prayers and Love</span><hr size=1> Twelve years ago tomarrow 4-27 Jaci you and Susan sang the song Follow Me at our wedding.  The words are<br>
Follow me up and down all the way and all around, take my hand and say you'll follow me.  Jaci we will take your <br>
hand and we will follow.  We love you.  Dan, Sam and<br>
Heidi we send our love and prayers.  Love, Charlotte, Kurt, Conrad and Matthew <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Bud  Barb</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/26/03 6:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Prayers &amp; Love</span><hr size=1> Dear Jaci,Dan,Sam,Heidi &amp; all of the family, I would like to share the following poem:<br>
       The tears flow freely down my cheek,<br>
       each drop a silent word to speak.<br>
       Sometimes when it's too hard to pray<br>
       my tears know just the words to say.<br>
      <br>
      Sometimes they whisper hurt and pain.<br>
      Sometimes they simply fall like rain.<br>
      More often they speak warmth and care<br>
      and you will find God's presence there.<br>
<br>
      I thank you God for tears that fall.<br>
      I thank you that you see them all.<br>
      The words are silent but they are there<br>
      each drop a silent liquid prayer.<br>
<br>
 We love you all.May God reach out &amp; give you his hand.We will be looking for that special star Jaci.Hugs all around.We love you &amp; pray for you all.Bud &amp; Barb                                          <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbudignet.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mbudig>mbudig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF9300>(4/26/03 7:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   be not afraid</span><hr size=1> Jaci,<br>
<br>
I remember singing this duet with you at the Methodist church in Owatonna.  I always loved singing with you and your beautiful voice gave me strength.  Perhaps these words will give you courage.<br>
<br>
You shall cross the barren desert,<br>
But you shall not die of thirst.<br>
You shall wander far in safety<br>
Though you do not know the way.<br>
You shall speak your words in foreign lands and all will understand.<br>
You shall see the face of God and live.<br>
<br>
Be not afraid.  I go before you always.<br>
Come, follow me.  And I will give you rest.<br>
<br>
If you pass through raging waters in the sea you shall not drown.<br>
If you walk amid the burning flames, you shall not be harmed.<br>
If you stand before the power of hell and death is at your side, <br>
Know that I am with you through it all.<br>
<br>
Be not afraid.  I go before you always. <br>
Come, follow me.  And I will give you rest.<br>
<br>
Blessed are the poor, for the kingdom shall be theirs.<br>
Blest are you that weep and mourn, for one day you shall laugh.<br>
And if wicked men insult and hate you all because of me,<br>
Blessed, blessed are you.<br>
<br>
Be not afraid.  I go before you always. <br>
Come, follow me.  And I will give you rest.<br>
<br>
All my love,<br>
Michelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> barbara Ivey</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/27/03 9:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thinking of you all</span><hr size=1> Dan, I read your letters to all of us with awe. I am so very impressed with the manner in which you, Heidi, and Sam, are able to keep  everything that is going on in such a wonderful perspective knowing that soon Jaci will be in the arms of the Lord. I can only hope that when I am faced with the same circumstances, I have even half the bravery and strength you have shown to your family and all your friends.   <br>
God bless all of you...Barb <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbudignet.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pufferk9>pufferk9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF9300>(4/27/03 9:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thinking of you all...</span><hr size=1> Dan, I read all your letters to everyone with awe. I stand in amazement at the courage and heart that you, Sam, and Heidi maintain. Your ability to keep looking ahead to Jaci's future in the arms of the Lord must be making Jaci's final days much more peaceful. I can only pray that when the time comes for me to go through this, I can  do it with half the grace that you all are showing to your family and friends. God bless you all....Barb  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> taylorbudignet</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/27/03 1:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Be Not Afraid</span><hr size=1> Jaci,<br>
Throughout your life you have always been a wonderful example of dignity and grace, and even now you continue by showing us how to approach death with the uppermost grace.<br>
<br>
I think of you often.  Recently I thought about the time when my father-in-law was nearing death and had asked me to sing at his funeral.  I had a lot of mixed emotions, so I went across the street to talk to you about my dilema.  You gave me the sheet music to &quot;Be Not Afraid&quot;, and the courage to sing it.  It is a beautiful song and was so fitting. Now that song will always bring you to mind.  When I saw Michelle's note, I thought &quot;Be Not Afraid&quot; truly is Jaci's song.<br>
<br>
Jaci--you have touched the lives of so many of us and we are all better people for having known you.  If it weren't for you, Elizabeth would never have become the pianist she is today.  You will always remain in our hearts.<br>
<br>
Love,<br>
Cindy and the rest of the Taylors <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Budig</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FF9300>(4/30/03 4:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   jaci</span><hr size=1> Dan, Jaci, Sam and Heidi:<br>
    Through this whole time with Jaci, I have felt so much love, devotion and strength.  Your whole family is really Blessed.  My prayers and thoughts are always with you.  Please keep us informed.<br>
In His name, Debbie K <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=41.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=41.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/prefabs/ez/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.threadControl?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/posticons/techops.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbudignetfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option val